\b \cf0 Global Action Bar
\b0 \
The Global Action Bar contains actions that are independent of the Content Area and that assist with high-level navigation of the application.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic 1__#$!@%!#__unknown.png \width17137 \height860
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs22 \cf0 \
\
The Global Action Bar contains...\
- A small branding area which will contain the Oracle "O" on the far left \'a0(\cf3 Branding area will likely need to be expanded\cf0 )\
- A "Home" action which will return the user to the Home page\
- A "Favorites" menu which will display a list of user objects that have been flagged as a favorite by the logged in user\
- A "Recent Items" menu which will display user objects that have been recently visited. \'a0Up to 20 recent objects shall be listed. \'a0\
- A Search control for searching all user (business) objects\
- A Settings action that will display a dialog containing user settings as well as administrative actions for users with those privileges\
- A Help action that will display Help content\
- A Logout action that will log the user out of the application\
\
- Tab navigation shall move from Home on the left to Logout on the right. \'a0\
- Down Arrow will display the Favorites or Recent Items menus when they have focus\
- Enter will execute any action with focus\
- Enter will execute a search when the focus is in the search input, or on the search execute action button\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Page Action Bar
\b0 \
The Page Action Bar contains actions that apply to the content on the page. \'a0For example, actions that apply to a requirement object, or a list of requirements. \'a0 \'a0 \'a0\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic 2__#$!@%!#__unknown.png \width11818 \height640
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs22 \cf0 \
\
- Actions that appear in the Page Action Bar must apply to a user object or user object list\
- Priority actions, either due to their frequent use, or importance shall be displayed as an independent action button\
- Actions of lessor priority shall be displayed in a More Actions menu\
\
- Tab navigation shall move from left to right across the actions\
- Enter will execute the action with focus\
- Down Arrow will display the More Actions menu\
- Arrow up / down will navigate the More Actions menu structure\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\b \cf0 Content Area
\b0 \
The Content Area will contain one of three pages; Home, Search Results or Object Details. \'a0Each page has a unique layout that will be described below. \'a0\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \ul \ulc0 Home\ulnone \
- The Home page will have a dashboard-like layout, essentially containing three panels that will display Action Items, Records owned by the logged in user and Activity updates on the objects that the user is a team member of. \'a0\
- The Open Action Items widget will display Open Action Items only. \'a0When the user clicks on "View All" will expand the widget to display closed action items for the user as well.\
- Records I own will display all active records that the user owns (\cf3 sort order to be determined\cf0 )\
- Clicking on an Object identifier in any widget will navigate the user to the object details for that object. \'a0\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

