\ul Search Results\ulnone \
The Search Results page will contain to areas. \'a0On the left will be the results list and on the right will be a Tag list that can be used to further filter the search results. \'a0\
- A title will display above the search results. \'a0The title shall be "Search results for "x"", where "x" is the entered search criteria\
- The search results will be displayed as a table. \'a0Ideally, the text that matches the search criteria will be highlighted for the user with bold, italicized text. \'a0\
- Clicking on an object identifier will navigate the user to the object details of the object. \'a0\
- Users shall be able to select table rows to execute page level actions (e.g. tag and export). \'a0To select a table row the user will be able to...\
\'a0\'a0-- Click on a row\
\'a0\'a0-- Use Shift-Click to toggle select contiguous rows\
\'a0\'a0-- Use Ctrl-Click to toggle select non-contiguous rows\
\'a0\'a0-- Use Ctrl-A to select all rows\
\
- The user can filter search results by attribute. \'a0Although this is pictured in the right area in this mock-up, it will be included as part of the table on the left. \'a0\
- The tags will be displayed as buttons that can be toggled on / off. \'a0This will allow users to toggle-on multiple tags to filter down on results that match multiple tags\
\
\
